node.title: In-person AI Meetup - GenAI, LLMs and Vector Search
node.description:
Pre-registration is required, please complete RSVP here:
[https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2023101701](https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2023101701)

Welcome to our monthly in-person AI meetup in Sydney. Join us for deep dive tech talks on AI/ML, food/drink, networking with speakers and fellow developers.

**Agenda:**

* 5:30pm\~6:00pm: Checkin, Food/drink and networking
* 6:00pm\~8:00pm: Tech talks
* 8:00pm: Q&A and Open discussion

**Tech Talk 1: AI-driven language processing with Vector Search**
**Speaker:** Erick Ramirez @DataStax
**Abstract:** ChatGPT opened the world to the significant advancement in natural language processing. Asking it questions as if talking to another human, it is able to deduce semantics and context to return relevant information. What if there was a way to retrieve data from your database not with SQL or SQL-like queries but with plain English questions? With a vector database like Cassandra, you can!
With vector search, data objects are transformed into embeddings â€“ vector representations in a high-dimensional space. The embeddings capture the semantic essence of data, enabling more nuanced searches. A vector search retrieves objects which are semantically-related, with an understanding of the context and meaning. Learn how to perform vector searches on your data out-of-the-box with Cassandra.

Stay tuned as we are updating speakers and schedules. If you have a keen interest in speaking to our community, we invite you to submit topics for consideration: [Submit Topics](https://forms.gle/JkMt91CZRtoJBSFUA)

**Partners/Sponsors:**
We are actively seeking sponsors to support our community. There are various ways to contribute, whether it is by offering venue spaces, providing refreshments, or becoming a cash sponsor. In return, sponsors will have the chance to speak at our meetups, receive prominent recognition as sponsors, and gain exposure through post-event emails sent to our extensive membership base of 3,000+ local or 300K+ developers worldwide.

**What you will learn:**

* **Agents:** Curious about agents with frameworks like Langchain and vector DBs? Want to know how to get work done and build apps that can do things weâ€™ve never been able to do before now?

* **Image Generators:** Image generators like Midjourney and Stable Diffusion have gotten stronger and stronger in record time. Learn to leverage them for max effect now.

node.title: Workshop: Cloud Native Threats Detection with Runtime Security
node.description:
Register on the event website to receive joining link: [https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2023072501](https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2023072501)

**Description:**
Participants of the workshop will receive a Certificate of Completion.

If you are looking to implement real time detection of unexpected behaviors, configuration changes and intrusions so you can stop attacks, then this is the workshop for you. Join this hands-on educational workshop to learn about runtime security and get up and running on Falco, the open-source standard for threat detection across Kubernetes, containers, hosts, and the cloud.

This session is for practitioners that are new to cloud-native and want to expand their knowledge of this dynamic area of security. We will introduce you to the concepts so you have the basics, but mostly you will be working on hands-on labs so you learn the tool and can implement it in your environment tomorrow.

node.title: LLMs: Beyond Proofs of Concept
NLP - From Prototype to Production, LLM/ChatGPT
node.description:
Register on the event website to receive joining link: [https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2023022402](https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2023022402)

**Description:**
What NLP in production actually looks like, including patterns, trends, challenges, use cases, and more.

Ines Montani is a software developer working on AI and NLP technologies. She is the co-founder and CEO of Explosion, where they make spaCy, one of the leading open-source libraries for Natural Language Processing in Python, and Prodigy, a modern annotation tool for creating training data for machine learning models.

In this fireside chat, Ines joins Hugo Bowne-Anderson, Outerboundsâ€™ Head of Developer Relations, to discuss what NLP in production actually looks like, including patterns, trends, challenges, use cases, and more.

After attending, you'll know:

* What NLP in production actually means;
* Trends and patterns in NLP use cases across industries (spaCy is used across finance, legal, medical, traditional manufacturing, e-commerce, customer service, media, energy, logistics, transport, and print media!);
* What skills data scientists and ML engineers need to build end-to-end NLP systems;
* What all the hype around large language models is, such as GPT-3, and how they can deliver real value in the world of NLP.
*

node.title: Fraud Detection with Graph Features and Graph Neural Networks
node.description:
Register here to receive zoom link: [https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2023013112](https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2023013112)

Why do we need Graph Features and Graph Neural Networks for Fraud Detection? See some reasons below:
\- Class Imbalance\, Label Scarcity & Fidelity \(Fraud cases are rare events\)
\- Fraud Camouflage \- handle context & feature inconsistency \(i\.e\. fraudsters connecting to regular entities\)
\- Investigation and Exploration \(visual way to connect the dots\)
\- Anomaly Detection \- handle point\, structural and contextual outliers
\- Graph Embeddings \- combined with NLP\, could be used for scalable fuzzy search and entity resolution
\- Explainability & fairness \- adding the context and structure for interpretation\, rebalancing the data to remove bias\.
That is why Facebook, Amazon, Tencent, Alibaba and eBay are using Graph for Fraud Detection.

node.title: ML Monthly Meetup: AutoML and Generative AI
node.description:
This is In-person + virtual event, please register on the event website to receive joining link: [https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2022121518](https://www.aicamp.ai/event/eventdetails/W2022121518)

**Agenda:**
\* 6:00pm\~6:30pm: Checkin, food and networking (In-person)
\* 6:30pm\~8:00pm: Tech talks (In-person + virtual)
\* 8:00pm\~8:30pm: Lucky Draw & Networking (In-person)

**Tech Talk 1: FLAML: A Fast Library for AutoML & Tuning**
**Abstract:** Machine Learning is a powerful and effective tool, but it takes tremendous effort to tune many choices such as hyperparameters to the problem at hand. This tuning process can be both difficult and costly. This talk will introduce an easy-to-use open-source library (https://github.com/microsoft/FLAML) built based on new cost-effective hyperparameter optimization and AutoML technologies from Microsoft Research. Both ML beginners and experts can benefit from this talk. Python or .NET programmers will learn how to use this lightweight library and related products to find accurate machine learning models automatically, efficiently, and economically.
**Speaker:** Chi Wang, Principal Researcher, Microsoft Research

**Tech Talk 2: Creating Generative Sitcom with Azure and OpenAI**
**Abstract:** The world of generative media is exploding. Pretty soon, we're going to be watching television shows, going to movies, and listening to music entirely generated by machines. Come learn about how Mismatch Media created Nothing, Forever, the world's first always-on, interactive television show generated through a combination of cloud services, machine learning techniques, and more. We'll do a technical deep dive into the architecture behind Nothing, Forever, the emerging state of generative media, and why Mismatch Media chose Azure as their cloud of choice.
**Speaker:** Skyler Hartle, Microsoft and co-founder of Mismatch Media
